tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Most parameters are within normal limits. However, creatinine is significantly elevated, suggesting impaired renal function, and chloride is mildly increased. Other kidney and metabolic markers (urea, electrolytes, glucose) are normal. Liver function, protein status, and lipid profile are unremarkable. Recommend clinical correlation and further evaluation of renal function.
